olution, and the post-1830 politics of protest. She re-creates the atmosphere of Restoration France and at the same time brings major nineteenth-century themes into focus: memory and commemoration, public and private spheres, politics and religion, anticlericalism, and the formation of democratic ideologies and practices.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aDemocracyxHistoryx19th centuryxFrance. 0aDemocracyzFrancexHistoryy19th century. 0aLegitimacy of governmentsxFrance. 0aLegitimacy of governmentszFrance. 0aMonarchyxHistoryx19th centuryxFrance. 0aMonarchyzFrancexHistoryy19th century. 7aHISTORY / Europe / General.2bisacsh  aanticlerical comedy.  aanticlericalism.  aclerics.  acomedy.  acultural history.  acultural studies.  adauphin.  ademocracy.  aecclesiastical officials.  aeurope.  afrench catholicism.  afrench comedy.  afrench history.  afrench revolution.  agovernment.  ahistory.  aking.  amonarchy.  apolitical engagement.  apolitical legitimacy.  apolitics.  apostrevolutionary france.  aprotest.  apublic spectacles.  aregime.  areign.  areligion.  arepresentative government.  arepublic.  arestoration.  arestored monarch.  arevolutionary period.  asatire.  asocial commentary.  atartuffe.  atheatricality.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092438340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520924383423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520924383/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles